<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Dear Friends - How to win on the 1st turn!<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(2.81)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=7964'>John "Jirving00" Irving</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=7964&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 8, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Hi,<br>
This article is meant to be read today, April 8th.<br>
As many of you may have noticed, the main post on decktech is about a broken card... &quot;Dear Friends&quot; from mines of moria. On the surface, the card blows. here it is.<br>
&quot;Exert a companion to place a free peoples card from your discard pile under your draw deck (2 cards if that character has the frodo signet).&quot;<br>
<br>
Alones, it sucks, but with 2 other cards... wealth of moria and hobbit appetite, you get an auto-win. (Wealth of Moria says &#39;spot a dwarf to check out the top 3 cards of your deck and take all free peoples cards into hand, and hobbit appetite says &#39;add X to heal a hobbit X times&#39;.<br>
<br>
How it is done:<br>
step 0: Start with Frodo, Son of drogo with Isildur&#39;s Bane and a dwarf.<br>
<br>
step 1: discard your whole deck. I&#39;ve heard you can use Beneath the mountains to accopmlish this on turn one, but that seems kinda janky to me.<br>
<br>
step 2: get 2 &quot;dear friends&quot; and 1 &quot;Wealth of moria&quot; in your hand.<br>
<br>
steps 3-3,000,000:<br>
here goes the loop (I hope this table show up right in the article). On the left collumn is the card you play, next collumns are # of exertions on frodo, # of cards in your deck, and # of relative cards in your hand, you start off with 0 exertions, 0 cards in deck, and 3 cards in hand (2x Dear Friends and Wealth of Moria). DF = Dear Friends, WM = Wealth of Moria, and HA = Hobbit Appetite. Note that at the begining of the loop, you only get Wealth of Moria and Dear Friends back with Dear Friends, cause you need to keep using them.<br>
<br>
KEY:<br>
action     Xert Deck Hand<br>
<br>
Starting   0    0    3<br>
<br>
DF         1    2    2<br>
DF         2    4    1<br>
WM         2    1    3<br>
DF         3    3    2<br>
WM         3    0    4<br>
DF         4    2    3<br>
HA         0    2    2<br>
DF         1    4    1<br>
WM         1    1    3<br>
DF         2    3    2<br>
WM         2    0    4<br>
DF         3    2    3<br>
DF         4    4    2<br>
HA         0    4    1<br>
WM         0    1    3<br>
DF         1    3    2<br>
WM         1    0    4<br>
<br>
*Starting  0    0    3<br>
<br>
*Wow, exiting isn&#39;t it? Well, you just proved that you can exert frodo to get any card you want from your discard pile to you hand, and if you can do it once, you can do it X times. once you do it 4 times you are left with 4 exertions and any 4 cards from your discard pile (whole deck) in your hand. Play another hobbit appetite (1 of the 4 cards you got) to heal frodo all the way again. You are now left with no result other than that you just got and 3 cards from your discard pile into your hand. You can therefore do it any amount of times... you do it 100 times. the 1st time to get gandalf, an elf, and whatever floats your boat (you just need those 2), the next 99 times you get a copy of your starting dwarf, a durin&#39;s secret, and What are we waiting for?. &quot;What are we waiting for&quot; says &#39;exert a dwarf to make opponent draw 2 cards, and then either discard 2 shadow cards or skip there next shadow phase.&#39; play this card 99 times or until they agree to skip there next 8 shadow phases (heal the dwarf with the copy every time after exerting), then play durrin&#39;s secret 7 times to make the move limit +7, allowing you to move to site 9 on turn 1 and you opponent never gets a shadow phase. But... this will all be errated within a week, so have fun while you can!<br>
<br>
see ya,<br>
